Rating: 3
Made this dish with some changes in the salsa. I used a can of diced tomatoes and used four cubes of frozen basil as I didn't have fresh. Also substituted dried marjoram, about 1/2 tsp. I simmered the salsa to reduce the liquid somewhat, approx. 15 minutes and served it warm with the fish. It was great this way and I plan to use it with shrimp. Will also double the ingredients and use as a side dish.

Rating: 3
Good solid recipe for summer grilling. I served the swordfish over steamed spinach and then topped it off with the salsa. I was out of marjoram, but went out on a limb with a small amount of mint---worked well. I also decided to take a tip from another recipe and marinated the swordfish in olive oil, lemon zest, lemon juice and chopped mint, for about an hour.

