Rating: 3
Appealing combination of flavors. I made the following changes: FOR SALSA: Omitted the balsamic vinegar, added dash of salt, used cherry tomatoes, removed seeds, but did not blanch or remove skin. MARINATED SWORDFISH in fresh lemon juice for 20 min. before broiling, then wiped dry with paper towels before applying oil. During last minute of broiling, piled the salsa on top of the swordfish pieces. I think the amount of balsamic vinegar in the recipe would have been too much.

