Rating: 0
I'm not the best when it comes to a grill, so I changed the cooking method to one that works for me. I make a mix of basil, oregano, fresh cracked black peeper, olive oil and balsamic vinegar and toss in tomato that has been peeled, seeded and chopped along with sliced black olives. I put the swordfish on a sheet of foil, top with the mixture, bake on a cookie sheet in a preheated 450 degree oven for 12 minutes. Serve atop your favoritd pasta and use the juices to moisten. And don't forget to heat some crusty bread to go with this!